cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses vulnerabilities in the LTE access network protocol specifications, which are related to security and privacy in mobile communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves network infrastructure and communication protocols, which suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the second likely category. The paper also discusses countermeasures and trade-offs, which are related to software engineering and system design, respectively, indicating cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the third and fourth likely categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of commercial LTE mobile devices, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as the fifth likely category.
